cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI 

The paper discusses the integration of science models in the retrieval process to enhance retrieval quality, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The specific approaches discussed, such as search term recommendation and author centrality, also have relevance to natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the implementation issues addressed in the paper could be relevant to database systems (cs.DB).
